trend_summary: 2000-2020 imagery shows scattered houses giving way to expanding subdivisions. Curvilinear streets spread from the centre, eating into fields and woodland, while a quarry area is partly revegetated. Agriculture retreats, tree cover becomes fragmented, but heavy industry remains limited. Net result is a modest rise in built-up footprint, keeping an overall low-rise suburban character.
notable_changes: Incremental growth of single-family subdivisions in the north-central and south-eastern sectors.
Addition of several new roads and cul-de-sacs, improving internal connectivity.
Conversion of multiple crop fields to housing and one rectangular recreational field.
Partial reclamation and greening of the central sand/gravel extraction pit.
Noticeable thinning and fragmentation of forest patches along development edges.
